  "text": "Inhibition in the PL activity and augmentation of lipolysis are being considered to be the effective ways in management of body weight [CITATION_1] . Present study revealed that, limitation in the absorption of lipid in the intestine is the potential mechanism by which the EECCL prevented weight gain in the HFD-fed rats. Previous studies also supported this hypothesis [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Therefore, in this study, the ability of EECCL to increase the excretion of fecal fat and consequently fecal fat energy excretion partially explained the observed significant reduction regarding body weight gain of the treated rats.",
